Floral baskets for Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Mustafa Kamal Helmi, chairman of the Egyptian Consultative Council, Youssef Amin Wali, general secretary of the National Democratic Party and deputy prime minister of Egypt, Diya Al Din Daud, general secretary of the Nasser Arab Democratic Party,  and the curator of the Military Museum separately visited the Korean embassy in Cairo and laid floral baskets before the portraits of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il there on the occasion of his 57th birthday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Floral baskets were also laid before the portraits at the DPRK embassies in Peru and Guyana by the general secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland), the international secretary of the Popular Action Party of Peru, the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, member of the parliament Rigoberto Esquera, the Peru-Korea Institute of Culture and Friendship, the Peruvian National Association for the Study of Kimjongilism, the Peruvian Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, the dean of a faculty of the Inca Garcilaso De La Vega University of Peru, the Guyanese National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea of Comrade Kim Il Sung and the Kim Jong Il class of Charlestown Senior Middle School, Georgetown, Guyana.   The central committee of the Lao Women's Union sent a floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Vientiane.
